      <h1 class='title'>Tax Law Rewrite</h1>
    </div>
    <div class='commons-written-statements-sitting' id='content'>
      
      <cite class='section'>HC Deb 30 October 2003 vol 412 cc15-6WS</cite>
      <a class='permalink column-permalink' id='column_15ws' title='Col. 15WS &mdash; HC Deb 30 October 2003 vol 412 c15WS' name='column_15ws' href='#column_15ws' rel='bookmark'>15WS</a>
      <div class='hentry member_contribution' id='S6CV0412P0-04188'>
        <a name='S6CV0412P0_20031030_CWS_3'>  </a>
        <blockquote cite='http://hansard.millbanksystems.com/people/ms-dawn-primarolo' class='contribution_text entry-content'>
          <a class='speech-permalink permalink' href='#S6CV0412P0_20031030_CWS_3' title='Link to this speech by Ms Dawn Primarolo' rel='bookmark'>&sect;</a>
          <cite class='member author entry-title'><a href="/people/ms-dawn-primarolo" title="Ms Dawn Primarolo">The Paymaster General (Dawn Primarolo)</a></cite>
          <p class="first-para" id="S6CV0412P0-04188">The tax law rewrite project at the Inland Revenue has completed its rewrite of the pay-as-you-earn (PAYE) regulations. The regulations were laid today. They were accompanied by a detailed commentary on them by the project. Copies of the commentary have been placed in the Library of the House.</p><p id="S6CV0412P0-04189">The rewritten regulations complement the modernisation of the legislation for employment income in the <a href="/acts/income-tax-earnings-and-pensions-act-2003">Income Tax (Earnings and Pensions) Act 2003</a>.</p><a class='permalink column-permalink' id='column_16ws' title='Col. 16WS &mdash; HC Deb 30 October 2003 vol 412 c16WS' name='column_16ws' href='#column_16ws' rel='bookmark'>16WS</a><p id="S6CV0412P0-04190">There will be no change in practice for employers and employees generally. But those who do use the regulations will find them clearer and more consistent.</p>
        </blockquote>
      </div>
